    parentName: "div"
  }, "Image by Gerd Altmann from Pixabay")), mdx("p", null, "I will follow up on the definition of mentoring from the introduction. If I were to define an ideal mentor, it would be someone very experienced in some area \u2014 such as public speaking \u2014 and willing to pass on the knowledge. On the other hand, the prot\xE9g\xE9 should be eager for knowledge that is often hard to find in books. When two such people meet, an incredible symbiosis can arise. For this to work, several conditions need to be met:"), mdx("ul", null, mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ul"
  }, "The base principle: the mentor must be interested in mentoring someone, and the prot\xE9g\xE9 must be interested in being mentored. In short, it is not possible without internal motivation"), mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ul"
  }, "If the prot\xE9g\xE9 is really motivated, he will find a mentor himself. He is aware of the value of information and is actively trying to obtain it"), mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ul"
  }, "The mentor must have only a limited number of prot\xE9g\xE9s (one, at most two) to be able to pay sufficient attention to everyone"), mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ul"
  }, "The mentor meets with his prot\xE9g\xE9 regularly at least once a week to discuss any problems. The mentor also acts as mental support"), mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ul"
  }, "The prot\xE9g\xE9 must be aware of the mentor\u2019s value and desire his valuable knowledge"), mdx("li", {
